# Employee Retention Initiative

This repository contains all documentation related to the Employee Retention Initiative at Green Destinations Travel Agency. 
The project focuses on analyzing and reducing employee attrition through targeted strategies that improve onboarding, engagement, career development, and communication.

## Folder Structure

- Vision and scope – Project vision and scope.  
- Stakeholder analysis – Identification and analysis of stakeholders.  
- Business requirements – Functional and non-functional requirements.  
- User story – User stories with acceptance criteria.  
- Process flows
          - Current (As-Is) 
          - Proposed (To-Be) process flows.  
- Data model – Data entities and relationships overview.  
- Business Regulations – Business rules guiding the initiative.  
- Risk and gap analysis – Risks and gaps identified.  
- Traceability matrix – Requirements traceability matrix.  
- BA plan – Business analysis plan and approach.  
- Root cause analysis – Root Cause Analysis identifying core reasons for attrition.


## How to Use
Review documents in sequence for a comprehensive understanding of the project. 
Process flows provide context for improvements. 
The traceability matrix links requirements to tests for quality assurance.


